---
description: core-be public API contract — route params, public ids, status policy, headers
globs:
  - "src/domains/**/*.routes.ts"
  - "src/domains/**/*.dto.ts"
  - "src/domains/**/*.controller.ts"
  - "tooling/openapi/**"
alwaysApply: false
---

- Path params: snake_case + semantic (`{plan_id}`, `{subscription_id}`, never `{id}`), registered in PARAM_NAME_TO_ENTITY; Zod params keys identical to the param name. The active organization is carried by the signed `org` JWT claim — routes do NOT take an `{organization_id}` path segment; the active-org resource is singular `/tenancy/organization` (sub-resources nest under it).
- Public ids: `<prefix>_<21 [a-z0-9]>` via generatePublicId(entity); external field name is always `id`; never write "public id" in docs.
- Body field casing: every request body property (`*.dto.ts` `z.object` keys) and response body property (`*.serializer.ts` output keys, plus the `errors[].field` value naming a body field) is **snake_case** (`file_name`, `created_at`), the external id stays `id`. Internal TS identifiers may stay camelCase. Exceptions (passed through verbatim): third-party / browser-native inbound payloads — Stripe webhooks, OAuth provider responses, WebAuthn W3C `navigator.credentials` JSON — and JWT claims. Enforced by `src/tests/unit/api/snake-case-body-keys.policy.unit.test.ts`.
- Status policy (middleware-enforced): GET 200, POST 201, PUT/PATCH 200, DELETE 204; webhooks + MCP stay 200. Update route-success-statuses.json with any route change.
- Error codes (full guide docs/reference/api/response-codes.md): 400 malformed shape only — every POST/PATCH/PUT has it; omit only on param-less query-less GET/DELETE; 401 token problems (recovery hint in message); 403 permission; 404 not-exists incl. cross-org; 409 state conflict (mutating); 422 business rule (incl. a capability unavailable for an immutable resource type — e.g. a personal org cannot gain members/roles/transfer/delete/billing → `assertTeamOrganization`, NOT 409) / idempotency payload mismatch (mutating); 413/415 body size/content-type (POST/PATCH/PUT); 429 everywhere with Retry-After + X-RateLimit-*; 500 never intentional. Never invent statuses outside this list.
- Methods/verbs: PUT = full replace, PATCH = partial merge (both 200); a collection action with no id is `POST /collection/verb` (e.g. transfer-ownership); a single-resource state change is `PATCH /resource/:id/state`.
- Personal vs team org: one shared route surface; team-only capabilities reject a personal org with **422** (`assertTeamOrganization`); every org response carries a type-derived `capabilities` object; the catalog `O` column (`both`|`team`) tracks `route-org-scope.json` (`validate:route-org-scope`). audit-logs naming: `/audit/logs` = platform-admin (global role), `/tenancy/organization/audit-logs` = org-scoped — both kept intentionally.
- Headers: Authorization Bearer (security scheme), X-Organization-Id, X-Idempotency-Key (required on the 13 idempotencyRequired writes — the `I`/`req` column in docs/routes.txt), X-Captcha-Token (public auth forms), X-CSRF-Token (refresh only), Stripe-Signature (Stripe-sent). All custom headers use X- forms; standards keep fixed names (Authorization, Stripe-Signature); ecosystem X- standards unchanged (X-Request-Id, X-Api-Key, X-CSRF-Token, X-RateLimit-*, X-Forwarded-For, X-Requested-With — the last is CORS-allowlisted so browser/XHR preflights pass).
- List endpoints: use the shared method in `src/shared/utils/http/list-query.util.ts` (`listSearchSortSchema` DTO + `resolveKeysetSort` + `buildSearchCondition` + `finishKeysetPage`; register the DTO in `tooling/openapi/query-schema-map.ts`; return `paginatedResponse`). `sort`/`order` (and `limit` on a route that didn't previously have it) must be `.optional()` NOT `.default(...)` — a defaulted Zod query param serializes as OpenAPI `required`, which oasdiff flags as `added the new required request parameter` (breaking); apply the default in the resolver/service instead. External-provider lists (Stripe) are a cursor passthrough (`limit` + `starting_after` + `has_more`), not the DB keyset. Searching a column on a FORCE-RLS joined table (e.g. `auth.users`) needs a SECURITY DEFINER resolver — see rls-tenant-isolation-guard.
- After any change: routes:catalog → docs:generate:multilang → docs:postman → docs:check + route-status gates (validate:route-success-statuses, validate:route-schema-docs, validate:route-org-scope). New/changed query params: `pnpm docs:breaking` (oasdiff).
